 {"id":"asupersync-1508v.2.3","title":"[SUPERSEDED] [AA-02.3] Validate shadow, canary, rollback, and evidence-ledger controller operations","description":"Create the explicit validation bead for decision-plane operations: shadow execution, canary gating, rollback drills, and evidence-ledger completeness for controller-driven runtime changes.","design":"Scope:\\n- Exercise promote/hold/rollback flows for representative controllers.\\n- Validate that fallback is instant, deterministic, and evidence-rich.\\n- Ensure logs, artifacts, and operator-facing diagnostics are good enough for real incidents.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Deterministic unit tests cover state transitions for shadow, canary, hold, rollback, and fallback.\\n2. Deterministic E2E scenarios prove controller promotion cannot bypass verification or evidence emission.\\n3. Structured logs and artifacts record policy ID, decision reason, fallback trigger, and replay pointers.\\n4. Failed rollouts produce direct, runnable recovery commands and leave the runtime in a conservative state.","notes":"Superseded by asupersync-1508v.2.6 after an interrupted shell pass created a duplicate task. Keep this issue only as audit history; the active canonical bead is asupersync-1508v.2.6.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:49:25.373909732Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-06T05:58:17.932443315Z","closed_at":"2026-03-06T05:58:17.932330415Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["aa02-decision-plane","alien-artifact","decision-plane","runtime-ascension","testing"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1508v.2.3","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1508v.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:49:25.373909732Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-1508v.2.3","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1508v.2.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:51:40.106545858Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1508v.2.4","title":"[AA-02.1] Define RuntimeKernelSnapshot and controller registration contract","description":"Define the canonical runtime snapshot that controllers are allowed to observe and the registration contract every controller must satisfy before it can participate in decisions.","design":"Scope:\\n- Specify snapshot fields, versioning, units, and update cadence.\\n- Include mandatory controller metadata: decisions made, fallback active, calibration score, last action, artifact IDs, and budget counters.\\n- Keep the seam narrow enough that the data plane remains deterministic and auditable.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Snapshot fields are versioned, typed, and documented with ownership and update rules.\n2. Registration validation rejects controllers with missing metadata or unsupported field expectations.\n3. Deterministic unit and E2E tests cover snapshot serialization, compatibility checks, upgrade or downgrade behavior, and deterministic update semantics.\n4. Structured logs expose snapshot IDs, version IDs, field provenance, and rejection reasons without leaking ambient authority or nondeterministic state.","notes":"Primary risk: overly broad snapshot surface.\\nCountermeasure: start with a strict minimum and add fields only with explicit justification.\\nFallback: controllers can consume a reduced snapshot and remain in shadow mode until richer fields exist.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:52:04.393495950Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-06T16:05:10.653087402Z","closed_at":"2026-03-06T16:05:10.653063357Z","close_reason":"Defined RuntimeKernelSnapshot/controller registration contract doc+artifact+smoke runner+invariants; validated via rch test","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["aa02-decision-plane","alien-artifact","decision-plane","formal","runtime-ascension"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1508v.2.4","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1508v.1.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:54:25.208239635Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-1508v.2.4","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1508v.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:52:04.393495950Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1508v.2.5","title":"[AA-02.2] Implement proof-carrying controller artifact format and verifier","description":"Implement the artifact format that packages controller policy tables, assumptions, bounds, compatibility ranges, fallback references, and verification material into one deterministic load unit.","design":"Scope:\\n- Define manifest schema, hash/signature chain, assumptions ledger, budget caps, and fallback pointer.\\n- Implement a verifier that rejects mismatched, stale, or incompatible artifacts before runtime use.\\n- Ensure artifact verification itself is deterministic and replayable.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Controller artifacts include manifest, compatibility, bounds, assumptions, and fallback metadata.\\n2. Loader/verifier rejects malformed or mismatched artifacts with deterministic diagnostics.\\n3. Unit and E2E tests cover happy path, signature/hash mismatch, version mismatch, and fallback activation.\\n4. Structured logs emit artifact IDs, verifier verdict, and rollback pointer.","notes":"Primary risk: artifact format becomes too clever to audit.\\nCountermeasure: keep manifests human-readable and verifiers fail-closed.\\nFallback: continue loading only built-in static policies if artifact verification is unavailable.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:52:09.371204836Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-06T16:15:10.051256453Z","closed_at":"2026-03-06T16:15:10.051230765Z","close_reason":"Implemented controller artifact format/verifier contract with deterministic cases, smoke runner, and invariant tests","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["aa02-decision-plane","alien-artifact","decision-plane","runtime-ascension","security"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1508v.2.5","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1508v.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:52:09.371204836Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"