+{"id":"asupersync-1508v.2.6","title":"[AA-02.3] Validate shadow, canary, rollback, and evidence-ledger controller operations","description":"Create the explicit validation bead for decision-plane operations: shadow execution, canary gating, rollback drills, and evidence-ledger completeness for controller-driven runtime changes.","design":"Scope:\\n- Exercise promote/hold/rollback flows for representative controllers.\\n- Validate that fallback is instant, deterministic, and evidence-rich.\\n- Ensure logs, artifacts, and operator-facing diagnostics are good enough for real incidents.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Deterministic unit tests cover state transitions for shadow, canary, hold, rollback, and fallback.\\n2. Deterministic E2E scenarios prove controller promotion cannot bypass verification or evidence emission.\\n3. Structured logs and artifacts record policy ID, decision reason, fallback trigger, and replay pointers.\\n4. Failed rollouts produce direct, runnable recovery commands and leave the runtime in a conservative state.","notes":"Primary risk: rollout logic is only tested on happy paths.\\nCountermeasure: make rollback drills and negative cases first-class.\\nFallback: disable promotion path and remain shadow-only until the validation bead is green.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"ubuntu","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:52:14.385208712Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-06T18:48:27.007648230Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["aa02-decision-plane","alien-artifact","decision-plane","runtime-ascension","testing"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1508v.2.6","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1508v.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:52:14.385208712Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-1508v.2.6","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1508v.2.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:54:30.295232795Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1508v.3","title":"[AA-03] Tail-Latency Calculus and Multi-Timescale Control","description":"Compile queueing/network-calculus/control-theory ideas into deterministic artifacts that govern scheduler, admission, retry, and cleanup behavior with better p99/p999 outcomes and explicit safety rails.","design":"Core idea:\\n- Treat p99 and p999 as a decomposition and control problem, not an after-the-fact benchmark score.\\n- Use service curves, queueing approximations, Lyapunov-style state objectives, and offline policy synthesis to drive bounded runtime decisions.\\n\\nTrack outputs:\\n- Queueing/network-calculus digital twin for major runtime paths.\\n- Offline synthesized control artifacts.\\n- Interference tests and multi-timescale safety doctrine.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Scheduler and related runtime stages have explicit queue/service models tied to observed workloads.\n2. Any new control policy is synthesized or calibrated offline, then compiled into deterministic runtime artifacts.\n3. Multiple controllers cannot ship without interference tests, timescale-separation notes, and fallback triggers.\n4. Tail-SLO claims are backed by workload replay, evidence bundles, and rollback criteria.\n5. The track ships deterministic unit and E2E validation packs, structured controller logs, and direct fallback/rerun commands so users get lower variance without opaque adaptive behavior.","notes":"Recommendation card:\\n- Change: make tail management an explicit control-plane responsibility.\\n- EV: extremely high because p99/p999 behavior dominates perceived runtime quality.\\n- Primary risk: oscillation from interacting controllers.\\n- Countermeasure: offline synthesis, bounded action sets, sequential validity checks, and forced conservative mode on drift.\\n- Conservative fallback: fixed current scheduler/admission parameters with advanced control disabled.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:44:25.146367257Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-06T06:56:57.352412012Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["aa03-control","alien-artifact","control","runtime-ascension","scheduler","tail-latency"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1508v.3","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1508v","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:44:25.146367257Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-1508v.3","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1508v.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:45:08.027508569Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1508v.3.1","title":"[SUPERSEDED] [AA-03.1] Build queueing/network-calculus digital twin for runtime hot paths","description":"Model the scheduler, drain, retry, wakeup, and admission paths as an explicit digital twin with service curves, queue approximations, and state variables tied to observed workloads.","design":"Scope:\\n- Translate the AA-01 taxonomy into model terms.\\n- Capture the dominant queues and service stages that drive p99/p999.\\n- Make the twin precise enough for offline policy search but honest about approximation error.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Major runtime paths have named queue/service stages with parameter sources.\\n2. Twin predictions can be compared against replayed workload evidence with disclosed error bounds.\\n3. Model artifacts are versioned and linked to workload IDs and snapshot fields.\\n4. Unit tests protect curve composition, model serialization, and comparator math.","notes":"Superseded by asupersync-1508v.3.4 after an interrupted shell pass created a duplicate task. Keep this issue only as audit history; the active canonical bead is asupersync-1508v.3.4.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:49:30.373246596Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-06T05:58:22.655017448Z","closed_at":"2026-03-06T05:58:22.654906121Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["aa03-control","alien-artifact","control","performance","runtime-ascension"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1508v.3.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1508v.1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:51:42.625006165Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-1508v.3.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1508v.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:51:45.091756389Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-1508v.3.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1508v.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:49:30.373246596Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1508v.3.2","title":"[SUPERSEDED] [AA-03.2] Synthesize bounded controller artifacts from replay data and state/loss models","description":"Use the digital twin and replay corpus to synthesize bounded controller artifacts for scheduler/admission/retry decisions with explicit state, action, and loss models instead of heuristic knob tuning.","design":"Scope:\\n- Define action sets small enough for deterministic runtime evaluation.\\n- Compile the chosen policy into artifact tables or small deterministic evaluators.\\n- Preserve conservative fallback and explicit comparator baselines.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Each synthesized controller states its states, actions, loss terms, and budget caps.\\n2. Generated artifacts are deterministic, versioned, and consumable by the AA-02 artifact system.\\n3. Before/after results are measured on replay workloads against named conservative comparators.\\n4. Unit tests protect policy-table determinism and reward/loss computations.","notes":"Superseded by asupersync-1508v.3.5 after an interrupted shell pass created a duplicate task. Keep this issue only as audit history; the active canonical bead is asupersync-1508v.3.5.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:49:35.423889125Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-06T05:58:27.413307556Z","closed_at":"2026-03-06T05:58:27.413180661Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["aa03-control","alien-artifact","control","decision-plane","runtime-ascension"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1508v.3.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1508v.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:49:35.423889125Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
