 {"id":"asupersync-1508v.5.2","title":"[SUPERSEDED] [AA-05.2] Prototype static leak checker and graded-budget pilot on restricted surfaces","description":"Implement the first restricted static safety tools for Asupersync: a leak checker that flags likely unresolved obligations and a graded-budget pilot that proves resource tracking is viable on a narrow surface.","design":"Scope:\\n- Use a deliberately restricted IR or API slice rather than promising universal coverage.\\n- Ensure diagnostics are deterministic and understandable.\\n- Demonstrate at least one compile-time or analysis-time catch that would otherwise rely on runtime discovery.","acceptance_criteria":"1. The leak checker or graded-budget pilot catches real misuse patterns on its target surface.\\n2. Diagnostics are deterministic and include stable locations, obligation kinds, and remediation hints.\\n3. Unit tests cover both sound positive detections and important non-findings.\\n4. Prototype outputs are clearly bounded: what is covered, what is intentionally out of scope, and what still needs runtime enforcement.","notes":"Superseded by asupersync-1508v.5.5 after an interrupted shell pass created a duplicate task. Keep this issue only as audit history; the active canonical bead is asupersync-1508v.5.5.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:50:05.209715552Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-06T05:58:55.687950273Z","closed_at":"2026-03-06T05:58:55.687845849Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["aa05-static-correctness","alien-artifact","formal","runtime-ascension","types"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1508v.5.2","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1508v.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-06T05:50:05.209715552Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
